message.content: This question requires knowledge about photosynthesis and the organisms that are capable of performing it. These organisms, collectively known as flora, have specialized cells called chloroplasts that contain the pigment chlorophyll, which is responsible for capturing sunlight during photosynthesis. Option (A) is incorrect because animals do not have the ability to perform photosynthesis. Option (B) is incorrect because inorganic minerals do not have cells.
